The VST measurement, derived from FST, is used to identify loci that differentiate by CN between populations [9]. VST and FST consider how genetic variation is partitioned at the individual, population, and global levels and range from 0 (no population differentiation) to 1 (complete population differentiation). VST has proven useful in identifying CNVs under positive selection in genetically distinct populations [8, 25, 51]. We calculated VST between VGIIa, VGIIb, and VGIIc groups for each non-overlapping 100 bp bin in the genome using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
